## Security Failure Causes

The attacker manipulated the system to deceive the contract into perceiving a higher liquidity level than it actually possessed.
To mitigate these risks, developers should follow best practices, conduct thorough security audits, and stay informed about emerging security issues in the blockchain and smart contract space. Additionally, using established security tools and frameworks, as well as involving experienced security professionals, can contribute to building more secure smart contracts.
